---
const process = [
  {
    title: "Diagnose",
    body: "Find the technical, content, analytics, and ownership issues behind the visible symptoms.",
  },
  {
    title: "Prioritize",
    body: "Separate urgent blockers from cosmetic noise.",
  },
  {
    title: "Fix",
    body: "Handle the useful work first instead of pretending every warning deserves panic.",
  },
  {
    title: "Measure",
    body: "Use Search Console, analytics, and live behavior to see what changed.",
  },
  {
    title: "Document",
    body: "Leave a trail: decisions, changes, risks, and next steps.",
  },
];
---

<section class="bg-warm-bone text-charcoal">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
      <p class="text-sm font-extrabold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-moss">
        How the hive works
      </p>
      <h2
        class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-normal text-charcoal md:text-5xl"
      >
        The hive works because every move has a job.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-muted">
        Boho uses internal systems to make the work faster and cleaner, but the
        logic stays visible: diagnose the system, prioritize the useful fixes,
        implement carefully, measure what changed, and document the trail.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-5">
      {
        process.map((step, index) => (
          <article class="rounded-lg border border-moss/15 bg-cream p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-extrabold text-honey">
              {String(index + 1).padStart(2, "0")}
            </p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-black text-charcoal">{step.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">{step.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 rounded-lg border border-moss/15 bg-white/80 p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-charcoal">Proprietary systems note</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
        Boho's internal systems are built for speed and consistency: audit
        patterns, triage flows, QA checklists, reporting formats, and
        agent-assisted research workflows. The client does not need to see every
        wrench in the drawer, but they should always understand the repair.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
